{{Infobox Person | name = Myra Curtis | image = Myra Curtis.jpg | image_size = | caption = portrait by [[Herbert James Gunn]] | birth_date = 2 October 1886 | birth_place = Sunderland | death_date = 27 June 1971 | death_place = Bognor Regis | death_cause = | residence = | other_names = | known_for = Principal of [[Newnham College]] | education = | employer = | occupation = | predecessor = [[Ruth Louisa Cohen]] | successor = [[Pernel Strachey]] | parents = George and Annie Curtis | relatives = | signature = | website = | footnotes = | nationality = [[United Kingdom]] }}
'''Dame Myra Curtis''' [[Order of the British Empire|DBE]] (1886–1971) was an [[Editing|editor]], [[civil servant]] and the principal of [[Newnham College, Cambridge]] from 1942 to 1954.<ref name=HDBW/><ref name=DNB/>
